    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-11-24T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-11-24T06:00:00-05:00" n="366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5787: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-24T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1924—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 24—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>455. My 452, November 21, 1 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>According to telephone message from Foreign Office Tuan Chi-jui assumed
                        office this morning as “Chief Executive of the Republic of China”. Message
                        also stated that official notification of this act would be conveyed to me
                        late tonight or tomorrow.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>American foreign adviser to Government states Cabinet has not turned over
                        its power to Tuan and that not yet decided whether Cabinet will continue to
                        function, tender its resignation to Tuan or surrender its power to new
                        Cabinet. I shall report further as <pb facs="0513" n="399" xml:id="pg_399"/>
                        soon as definite information available regarding exact status of
                        Government.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Chang Tso-lin arrived Peking today with some thousand troops. Peking is
                        quiet.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Repeated to Tokyo.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
